    h3.h3.font-weight-bold Epollo Content Policy
    p
      | Epollo is a platform for everyone to write, read, and share knowledge. The nature of it&apos;s content might be funny, serious, offensive, or anywhere in between. While participating, it&rsquo;s important to keep in mind this value above all others: show enough respect to others so that we all may continue to enjoy Epollo for what it is.
    h4.h4.font-weight-bold Unwelcome content
    p
    | While Epollo generally provides a lot of leeway in what content is acceptable, here are some guidelines for content that is not. Please keep in mind the spirit in which these were written, and know that looking for loopholes is a waste of time.
    h5(style='margin-top:10px;') Content is prohibited if it
    ul
      li Is illegal
      li Is involuntary pornography
      li Is sexual or suggestive content involving minors
      li Encourages or incites violence
      li Threatens, harasses, or bullies or encourages others to do so
      li Is personal and confidential information
      li Impersonates someone in a misleading or deceptive manner
      li
        | Uses Epollo to solicit or facilitate any transaction or gift involving certain goods and services
      li Is spam
    br
    h5 Prohibited behavior
    | In addition to not submitting unwelcome content, the following behaviors are prohibited on Epollo
    ul
      li Asking for votes or engaging in vote manipulation
      li Breaking Epollo or doing anything that interferes with normal use of Epollo
      li Creating multiple accounts to evade punishment or avoid restrictions
    br
    | If a user of Epollo does something that goes against our Content Policy, the moderators of Epollo can do the following in order with the user.
    ul
      li Asking you nicely to knock it off
      li Asking you less nicely
      li Temporary or permanent suspension of accounts
      li Removal of privileges from, or adding restrictions to, accounts
      li Adding restrictions to share content
      li Removal of content
      li Banning from Epollo
